messages.content:
{
    "thought_on_cooking_style": "The cooking style presented in the given recipes is very hands-on and descriptive, focusing on the sensory aspects of cooking, such as sight, smell, and touch. The recipes emphasize the importance of observing changes in the ingredients as they cook, adjusting seasoning to taste, and using techniques like browning, simmering, and baking to develop flavors. The style also suggests a home-cooked approach with a touch of professional finesse, particularly in the presentation and finishing touches.",
    "thought_on_recipe": "Based on the provided examples, the recipe I will create will follow a step-by-step approach, guiding the cook through each stage of the process with attention to detail. The recipe will incorporate simple yet flavorful ingredients, and the steps will include sensory cues to help the cook understand when to move on to the next stage. The goal is to create a dish that is both approachable for home cooks and impressive enough to serve to guests.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title": "Garlic Butter Shrimp Pasta",
            "description": "This recipe is for a delightful garlic butter shrimp pasta that combines succulent shrimp with a rich and aromatic garlic butter sauce, tossed with al dente spaghetti and finished with fresh parsley and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese. It's a simple yet elegant dish perfect for a weeknight dinner or a special occasion.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Begin by bringing a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add half a pound of spaghetti and cook according to the package instructions until al dente, usually about 8 to 10 minutes."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the pasta cooks, heat two tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add one pound of cleaned and deveined shrimp to the skillet, cooking until the shrimp turn pink and opaque, about 2 to 3 minutes per side."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Remove the shrimp from the skillet and set aside. In the same skillet, add three tablespoons of unsalted butter and let it melt. Add four cloves of minced garlic to the butter and saut until fragrant, about 1 minute, being careful not to burn the garlic."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Pour in half a cup of chicken or vegetable stock to deglaze the skillet, using a wooden spoon to scrape up any browned bits from the bottom. Allow the mixture to simmer for 2 minutes to reduce slightly."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Return the shrimp to the skillet and toss to coat in the garlic butter sauce. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Drain the cooked spaghetti, reserving a cup of the pasta cooking water. Add the spaghetti to the skillet with the shrimp and toss to combine with the sauce, adding a bit of the reserved pasta water if needed to loosen the sauce."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Finish the dish by stirring in a handful of chopped fresh parsley and a generous sprinkle of grated Parmesan cheese. Adjust seasoning if necessary."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Serve the garlic butter shrimp pasta hot, garnished with additional parsley and Parmesan cheese if desired."
                }
            ]
        }
}
